# This script assembles a fully-formed, ready-to-run Aethereal Command Center
# with a sleek chat UI and a Node.js orchestrator that fans out to multiple

# Aethereal Command Center (Chat + Orchestrator)

Sleek, lab-clean UI + multi-agent chat that routes to your local LLM fleet (LM Studio / Ollama).
The **Director** orchestrates subagents (Researcher, DB Manager, Strategist, Architect, Engineer, Marketing)

## One-shot start (Windows / macOS / Linux)
```bash

Default endpoints

  • LM Studio (OpenAI compatible): http://localhost:1234/v1

Models

MCP & Tools

No DB required (in-memory + JSON logs). Swap server/storage later for Qdrant/SQLite/etc.

index_js = r"""
import express from "express";
import cors from "cors";
import dotenv from "dotenv";
import fs from "fs";
import path from "path";
import { fileURLToPath } from "url";

dotenv.config();
const __filename = fileURLToPath(import.meta.url);
const __dirname = path.dirname(__filename);

const app = express();
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 8787;

app.use(cors());
app.use(express.json({ limit: "2mb" }));

// --- Load config
function loadJSON(p) {
return JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(p, "utf-8"));
}
const providersCfgPath = path.join(__dirname, "config", "providers.json");
const agentsCfgPath = path.join(__dirname, "config", "agents.json");
let providersCfg = loadJSON(providersCfgPath);
let agentsCfg = loadJSON(agentsCfgPath);

// Resolve env var templates like ${VAR:-default}
function resolveEnvTemplates(s) {
return s.replace(/${([A-Z0-9_]+)(:-([^}]*))?}/g, (_, key, _all, def) => {
const v = process.env[key];
return (v !== undefined && v !== "") ? v : (def || "");
});
}
for (const [, p] of Object.entries(providersCfg.providers)) {
p.baseUrl = resolveEnvTemplates(p.baseUrl);
if (p.apiKey) p.apiKey = resolveEnvTemplates(p.apiKey);
}

let providerModels = {}; // { providerName: [modelIds...] }

async function fetchModelsForProvider(pname) {
const p = providersCfg.providers[pname];
if (!p) return [];
try {
const res = await fetch(p.baseUrl + "/models", {
headers: p.apiKey ? { "Authorization": Bearer ${p.apiKey} } : {}
});
if (!res.ok) throw new Error("models fetch failed " + res.status);
const data = await res.json();
const list = (data.data || []).map(x => x.id);
providerModels[pname] = list;
console.log([models] ${pname}: ${list.join(", ") || "(none)"});
return list;
} catch (e) {
console.warn([models] ${pname} error:, e.message);
providerModels[pname] = [];
return [];
}
}

async function refreshAllModels() {
for (const pname of Object.keys(providersCfg.providers)) {
await fetchModelsForProvider(pname);
}
}
await refreshAllModels();

function pickModel(pname, preferred) {
const list = providerModels[pname] || [];
if (preferred && list.includes(preferred)) return preferred;
if (list.length > 0) return list[0];
return preferred || "unknown-model";
}

function getProviderHeaders(p) {
const h = { "Content-Type": "application/json" };
if (p.apiKey) h["Authorization"] = Bearer ${p.apiKey};
return h;
}

async function openaiChat(pname, model, messages, opts={}) {
const p = providersCfg.providers[pname];
if (!p) throw new Error("unknown provider " + pname);
const body = {
model,
messages,
temperature: opts.temperature ?? 0.7,
max_tokens: opts.max_tokens ?? 1024,
stream: false
};
const res = await fetch(p.baseUrl + "/chat/completions", {
method: "POST",
headers: getProviderHeaders(p),
body: JSON.stringify(body)
});
if (!res.ok) {
const t = await res.text();
throw new Error(provider ${pname} error ${res.status}: + t);
}
const data = await res.json();
const content = data?.choices?.[0]?.message?.content ?? "";
return content;
}

// --- Tools subsystem
import { ddgJson } from "./tools/ddg.js";
const Tools = {
"web.search": ddgJson,
};

// --- Basic health
app.get("/health", (_req, res) => res.json({ ok: true, time: new Date().toISOString() }));

// --- List providers / models
app.get("/api/providers", (_req, res) => {
res.json({
default_provider: process.env.DEFAULT_PROVIDER || providersCfg.default_provider,
providers: Object.fromEntries(Object.entries(providersCfg.providers).map(([k, v]) => [k, { baseUrl: v.baseUrl, models: providerModels[k] || [] }]))
});
});

// --- List agents
app.get("/api/agents", (_req, res) => {
res.json(Object.values(agentsCfg));
});

// --- Tool invoke
app.post("/api/tool", async (req, res) => {
const { name, input } = req.body || {};
if (!name || !(name in Tools)) return res.status(400).json({ error: "unknown tool" });
try {
const out = await Toolsname;
res.json({ ok: true, output: out });
} catch (e) {
res.status(500).json({ ok: false, error: e.message });
}
});

// --- Chat routing
async function callAgent(agentName, userText, context={}) {
const agent = agentsCfg[agentName];
if (!agent) throw new Error("unknown agent " + agentName);
const model = pickModel(agent.provider, agent.preferred_model);
const msgs = [
{ role: "system", content: agent.system },
{ role: "user", content: userText }
];
if (context && Object.keys(context).length) {
msgs.push({ role: "user", content: Context:\n${JSON.stringify(context, null, 2)} });
}
const out = await openaiChat(agent.provider, model, msgs);
return { agent: agentName, model, output: out };
}

async function directorOrchestrate(userText) {
// 1) Researcher tries to find info (uses tool hint in context)
const research = await callAgent("Researcher", userText + "\nIf web data helps, say 'NEED_WEB' with 3-5 key queries.", {});
let researchToolOut = null;
if ((research.output || "").toUpperCase().includes("NEED_WEB")) {
// naive extract: take lines after NEED_WEB
const lines = research.output.split("\n").map(s => s.trim()).filter(Boolean);
const q = lines.slice(1, 6).join(" ");
try {
researchToolOut = await Tools["web.search"]({ q });
} catch {}
}

// 2) Strategist synthesizes
const stratCtx = { research: research.output, web: researchToolOut };
const strat = await callAgent("Strategist", userText, stratCtx);

// 3) DB Manager proposes data flows
const dbm = await callAgent("DBManager", userText, stratCtx);

// 4) Architect + Engineer + Marketing weigh in
const [arch, eng, mkt] = await Promise.all([
callAgent("Architect", userText, stratCtx),
callAgent("Engineer", userText, stratCtx),
callAgent("Marketing", userText, stratCtx),
]);

// 5) Director final
const director = await callAgent("Director", userText, {
research: research.output,
web: researchToolOut,
strategist: strat.output,
db: dbm.output,
architect: arch.output,
engineer: eng.output,
marketing: mkt.output
});

return { research, researchToolOut, strat, dbm, arch, eng, mkt, director };
}

app.post("/api/chat", async (req, res) => {
const { agent="Director", text="", fanout=false } = req.body || {};
if (!text) return res.status(400).json({ error: "missing text" });
try {
if (agent === "Director" or agent === "Director (All)" or fanout) {
const out = await directorOrchestrate(text);
return res.json({ ok: true, mode: "director", ...out });
}
// single agent
const single = await callAgent(agent, text, {});
res.json({ ok: true, mode: "single", result: single });
} catch (e) {
console.error(e);
res.status(500).json({ ok: false, error: e.message });
}
});

app.listen(PORT, () => {
console.log([Aethereal] Server running on http://localhost:${PORT});
});
"""

ddg_js = r"""
// Simple DuckDuckGo JSON query
export async function ddgJson(input) {
const q = typeof input === "string" ? input : (input?.q || "");
if (!q) return { query: "", results: [] };
const url = "https://api.duckduckgo.com/?format=json&no_redirect=1&no_html=1&q=" + encodeURIComponent(q);
const res = await fetch(url);
if (!res.ok) throw new Error("duckduckgo api error " + res.status);
const data = await res.json();
// Very light shaping
const out = {
heading: data.Heading || "",
abstract: data.Abstract || "",
results: (data.RelatedTopics || []).slice(0, 8).map((t) => ({
text: t.Text || "",
url: t.FirstURL || ""
}))
};
return out;
}
"""
(server/"tools/ddg.js").write_text(ddg_js, encoding="utf-8")
